TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi beforefieldinit Shapetype extends DocumentFormat.OpenXml.OpenXmlCompositeElement

summary.para: Shape Template.
This class is available in Office 2007 or above.
When the object is serialized out as xml, it's qualified name is v:shapetype.

remarks.format:
## Remarks [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlnoticeiso.md)]
`shapetype (Shape Template)`
This element defines a shape template that can be used to create other shapes. Shapetype is identical to the shape element (§14.1.2.19) except it cannot reference another shapetype element. The type attribute shall not be used with shapetype. Attributes defined in the shape override any that appear in the shapetype. positioning attributes (such as *top*, *width*, *z-index*, *rotation*, *flip*) are not passed to a shape from a shapetype. To use this element, create a shapetype with a specific id attribute. Then create a shape and reference the shapetype's id using the type attribute.
[*Example*:
```xml <v:shapetype id="mytype" fillcolor="silver" strokecolor="blue"> <v:path v="m 0,1000, 1000,1000, 1000,0 x e"/> <v:fill on="true" type="gradient" color2="navy" angle="-45"/> </v:shapetype> <v:shape type="#mytype" style="position:absolute;top:10;left:10;width:50;height:50"/> <v:shape type="#mytype" fillcolor="teal" style="position:absolute;top:10;left:75;width:75;height:50"/> <v:shape type="#mytype" style="position:absolute;top:10;left:165;width:50;height:50"> <v:fill type="solid"/> </v:shape> <v:shape type="#mytype" path="m 1000,1000 0,1000 x e" style="position:absolute;top:10;left:230;width:50;height:50"/> ```
